verbose_text: Systemic CNO (1.0 mg/kg) significantly increased CS elicited freezing levels in trained hM3Dq expressing animals compared with mCherry expressing animals (F (2, 20) = 69.54, * * * * p < 0.0001, Tukey 's MCT : hM3Dq untrained versus mCherry trained, * * * * p < 0.0001, hM3Dq untrained versus hM3Dq trained, * * * * p < 0.0001, mCherry trained versus hM3Dq trained, * * * p < 0.001), with minimal CS elicited freezing responses observed in the untrained control group.
evidence: CNO (1.0 mg/kg) significantly increased CS-elicited freezing levels in trained hM3Dq
